images:
A highly detailed, technical blueprint-style developer infographic poster on the theme of "AGENTFORCE ACTION TYPES".
Overall Theme: High-tech dark mode developer dashboard, cybersecurity blueprint, with sharp glowing lines and neat borders.
Colors: Deep dark navy background with glowing neon blue, electric cyan, warning red, and success green highlights.

Header:
- A prominent top-center glowing blue header: "AGENTFORCE ACTION TYPES".
- Below it, a clean subtitle: "Apex, Flow, Prompt Template, and API — What Each One Is For" with a small Salesforce logo on the top-left and an "APEX BEST PRACTICES" badge on the top-right.

Section 1: "WHY IT MATTERS" (Top Row, 3 Horizontal Cards)
- "Single Responsibility" with a target icon, "Typed Contracts" with a shield icon, "Atlas Orchestrates" with a bot icon

Section 2: "THE COST" (Middle Row, Side-by-Side Comparison)
- Left Box (Red Theme): "WRONG: One God Action Does Everything". Shows a red status pill "DANGER — ANTI-PATTERN".
- Right Box (Green Theme): "RIGHT: Single-Purpose Typed Actions". Shows a green status pill "SUCCESS — BEST PRACTICE".

Section 3: "CODE PATTERNS" (Main Center)
- Left Column (Bad Code in Red Border):
  - Heading: "// BAD"
  - Code block:
    @InvocableMethod(label='Handle Everything')
public static List<String> doAll(List<Request> r) {
  // triage + entitlement + email + update + notify
  // 400ms, untestable, can never be reused
}
- Right Column (Good Code in Green Border):
  - Heading: "// GOOD"
  - Code block:
    @InvocableMethod(label='Classify Case Type')
public static List<ClassifyResult> classify(
  List<ClassifyRequest> requests
) {
  // Single job. Typed input. Typed output.
  // Reused by Agentforce + Flow + LWC
}

Section 4: "DEVELOPER PROFILE & CHECKLIST" (Bottom Row)
- Left Side: A 3D Pixar-style cartoon avatar portrait of a dark-skinned South Asian male with a full thick black beard, shoulder-length wavy dark hair pulled up into a messy top bun, warm friendly smile showing teeth, wearing a grey crew-neck sweatshirt with the word "MAGNETIC" on it, set against a warm orange bokeh background. The avatar is labeled "Bennie Joseph | Salesforce Architect". Next to it is a quote bubble: "Architecting intuitive systems, engineering scalable solutions."
- Right Side: A checklist with points: "One action = one business capability", "Always use @InvocableMethod with typed Request/Response", "Return confidence score + reason for Atlas to route", "Test each action with 200-record bulk scenarios", "Register action in Agentforce Builder with clear description".
- Footer: A thin bar with icons for "Agentforce 2.0", "Atlas Reasoning", "Apex Actions", "Flow Actions" and the text "CODE SMART. AUTOMATE FASTER. DELIVER EXCELLENCE."

Style Details: Super high resolution, technical drawing grid, razor-sharp white and neon text, crisp layout, developer IDE aesthetic, flat vector graphics with subtle glow, highly legible monospace font for code blocks, professional presentation.
